Title: L’air de l’eau (The Air of Water). Artist: ['Alberto Giacometti', 'Georges Hugnet']. Nationality: Swiss. Gender: male. Artist born: 1901. Date created: published 1934; binding 1937. Medium: Book with four engravings with chine collé; letterpress text; one handwritten poem by Breton in ink; publisher’s original printed-paper cover bound in; publisher’s prospectus tipped in. Bespoke binding designed by Hugnet and fabricated by Christy: covers with goat leather, blind tooling, and foil blocking, front and back each holding liquid mercury and hand-cut glass shapes between two panes of glass (back cover accidentally cracked in 1940 causing mercury to be lost); decalcomania in gouache on paper endleaves; silk-ribbon bookmark.. Dimensions: Book (closed): 10 1/16 × 9 1/8 × 15/16 in. (25.5 × 23.1 × 2.4 cm); 
pages: 9 5/8 × 8 7/8 in. (24.5 × 22.5 cm);
engravings: 6 3/8 × 5 3/8" (16.2 × 13.7 cm)
. Classification: Illustrated Book. Department: Drawings & Prints. Acquired by MoMA: 2022-05-24. Credit: Gift of Helen and Sam Zell
